  "eprint": {
    "title": "Indifferentiability of SKINNY-HASH Internal Functions",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Akinori Hosoyamada",
        "email": "bh@hco",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Tetsu Iwata",
        "email": "akinori@nagoya-u",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "We provide a formal proof for the indifferentiability of SKINNY-HASH internal function from a random oracle.\nSKINNY-HASH is a family of function-based sponge hash functions,\nand it was selected as one of the second round candidates of the NIST lightweight cryptography competition.\nIts internal function is constructed from the tweakable block cipher SKINNY.\nThe construction of the internal function is very simple and the designers claim $n$-bit security, where $n$ is the block length of SKINNY.\nHowever, a formal security proof of this claim is not given in the original specification of SKINNY-HASH.\nIn this paper, we formally prove that the internal function of SKINNY-HASH has $n$-bit security, i.e., it is indifferentiable from a random oracle up to $O(2^n)$ queries, substantiating the security claim of the designers.",
    "keywords": [
      "provable security",
      "sponge construction",
      "indifferentiability",
      "SKINNY",
      "SKINNY-HASH"
    ],
    "category": "Secret-key cryptography",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
    "last_updated": "2020-11-02",
    "license": "CC BY",
    "related_papers": []
